A total of 703 HCWs were recruited; 104 HCWs who reported receipt of pH1N1 vaccine were excluded from the following analyses. Among the 599 HCWs who reported that they had not received pH1N1 vaccine, 74 (12%) had pH1N1 antibody titre ≥1:40 by VN. In a random sample of 59/599 tested by HAI, 9 (15%) had antibody titre ≥1:40. There was a significant difference in the proportion of HCWs with antibody titre ≥1:40 by age, with greater proportion among younger HCWs, and by occupation, with greater proportion among doctors compared with nurses (Table I
). In a multivariate analysis, age remained significantly associated with an antibody titre ≥1:40 and HCWs working in the emergency room had a marginally significant higher probability of antibody titre ≥1:40 (P
 = 0.06) (Table II
).
